summary: 26 publicly accessible Game of Thrones filming locations
title: 26 publicly accessible Game of Thrones filming locations
body:
26 publicly accessible Game of Thrones filming locations

Game of Thrones is a huge tourism draw for our millions of annual visitors to NI. I talk to some every weekend at my stall in St George’s Market, and they pretty much have the same itinerary, the market (of course!), Titanic and that stunner of a coastline including Giants Causeway, Carrick-a-rede and the Dark Hedges. They jump on daily coaches to take them on a Game of Thrones tour and to visit…

summary: Inspired by one of my favorite moments in Game of Thrones ever, when [SPOILER] Daenerys finally makes it to Dragonstone....
caption:
Inspired by one of my favorite moments in Game of Thrones ever, when [SPOILER] Daenerys finally makes it to Dragonstone. Although she has finally reached the destination she has talked about for years, she knows that this is only the beginning, and everything that she had to go through to get there was just giving her the knowledge and experience to fight and win the wars to come.
It’s a wonderful metaphor-I think. A bachelors degree is a huge accomplishment, but it’s only just the beginning.

I feel like the fight would of been more emotional if Gregor still had some coherent activity in his brain.

A battle of brothers who have a cruel history finally giving into their anger and fighting to the death sounds more dramatic than…….The hound killing an zombie giant that used to be his brother.

What do you guys think?
